    "body": "Replace works off of a pattern / regex. Keep in mind that `'.0'` as a regex means \"match any character followed by a 0\", hence why your second and fourth entries are getting fully replaced as they match the pattern twice.\r\n\r\nIf you wanted to match a literal period you need to escape it in your regex\r\n\r\n```python\r\nIn [8]: pd.Series(['41.0', '40.0', '35.0', '30.0']).str.replace('\\.0', '')\r\nOut[8]: \r\n0    41\r\n1    40\r\n2    35\r\n3    30\r\ndtype: object\r\n```\r\n\r\n"
